## Conversation
Final PR of the v2 stack, per review comments on #7178: the tsi alias (and
the bindings module's temporary SDK re-export that let migration diffs keep
their tsi.X references) is a migration step only; this PR removes it.

## Actions
- Branch was RESET to the amended #7178 tip and the conversion REGENERATED
  (the previous PR C commit predated the superset-alias amendment and would
  have conflicted on every import line).
- Script-converted 18 alias files: collected tsi.X references, partitioned by
  hasattr(weave_server_sdk.models, X) into SDK vs gap names, emitted two
  direct import blocks, stripped prefixes; collision-checked per file.
  Binding: 139 SDK + 67 gap names — explicit by design.
- Removed the explicit SDK re-export block from bindings/models.py (added in
  the #7178 amendment); its internal alias became direct named imports.

## Errors & Mistakes
- Earlier in the amendment: `from weave_server_sdk.models import *` re-export
  SHADOWED the bindings module's own `import datetime` (the SDK module
  exports its `from datetime import datetime` import) — broke every
  datetime.datetime annotation at import time. Star imports of generated
  modules leak their imports; the re-export had to be an explicit name list.

